<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n38210c"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n38" href="#n38210c">N38 (VI.B.32)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n38all.htm#n38210c"> 210(c)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> <font face="wake">X</font> revolution of word / marriage &mdash; &mdash; </blockquote> <dd class="well"><mm class="note">Note: Revolution of the Word. A proclamation drawn up by Eugene Jolas and signed by himself and fifteen others. It consisted of twelve propositions, of which the first was &lsquo;THE REVOLUTION IN THE ENGLISH LANGUAGE IS AN ACCOMPLISHED FACT&rsquo; and the last &lsquo;THE PLAIN READER BE DAMNED&rsquo;. It appeared in June 1929 on the opening page of the double issue of <cite>transition</cite> 16/17. </mm> </dd></dl>
